Following the demise of Hon Tunde Braimoh in the early hours of Friday, the Lagos State House of Assembly has announced suspension of legislative activities for one week. The Clerk of the House, Mr Azeez Sanni who disclosed this in a circular to members said legislative activities would resume on July 20, this year. According to him, “All committee meetings, assignments and visits to Lagos State House of Assembly is hereby suspended from Monday July, 13 to Sunday July 1, 2020”. Until his death, Braimoh was the member representing Kosofe State Constituency 2 in the Assembly and Chairman of the Committee on Information, Strategy and Security and a second term lawmaker. In the 8th Assembly, he was first the Chairman of Committee on Information, Strategy and Security before becoming Chairman of the Committee on Human Rights, Public Petitions, Justice and LASIEC. Between 1999 and 2002, he was elected Chairman of Kosofe Local Government. Popularly called ‘Big Daddy’, Braimoh was very popular, not only among his colleagues and politicians but also among the social circle in Lagos. As a Muslim, he was buried on Friday at about 2.30 p.m at Ikoyi Cemetery.